        "id": 1000898
      },
      "writtenOn": "2014-06-03T05:50:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "yes, surprisingly.\n\nAlso, for ARM and x86, it\u0027s a big difference to write:\n\n-----------\nconst int bit \u003d (value \u003e split);\nif (value \u003e split) { ... }\n-----------\n\ninstead of\n\n-----------\nconst int bit \u003d (value \u003e split);\nif (bit) { ... }\n-----------\n\nAnd, eventually for x86, it\u0027s even better to\nnot use a \u0027const int bit\u0027, but just \u0027int bit\u0027 like at line 148.\n\nIt\u0027s also a big speed diff to store \u0027range\u0027 at 131 *before* calling\nVP8LoadNewBytes(br), instead of moving line 131 to 136 like expected.\n\n\n\u003d\u003e added few comments about that.",
      "parentUuid": "AAAAdn//nGo\u003d",
